7. Conclusion

ST‑T1024 introduces Assured Execution Time (AET) — a paradigm shift from worst‑case estimation to physically assured execution. By replacing stochastic inference with a deterministic, FSM‑orchestrated, ternary‑quantized pipeline, ST‑T1024 achieves:

· ✅ AET = WCET — no over‑approximation
· ✅ ≤ 800 ns — physically enforced
· ✅ 3.7 µJ — ultra‑low energy
· ✅ Zero hallucination — deterministic outputs

To our knowledge, this is the first time a physically assured execution time has been achieved in an AI inference architecture, and one of the first in the history of hard real‑time embedded systems.

The standard is open. The physics is settled. The assurance is real.

